# Summary of FRED Data for ICE BofA 7-10 Year US Corporate Index Effective Yield

## Key Facts and Statistics:

**Recent Daily Observations (in percent):**
- 2026-02-16: 4.85
- 2026-02-13: 4.86
- 2026-02-12: 4.89
- 2026-02-11: 4.96
- 2026-02-10: 4.93

**Series Details:**
- Units: Percent
- Frequency: Daily, Close
- Seasonal Adjustment: Not Seasonally Adjusted
- Source: ICE Data Indices, LLC
- Release: ICE BofA Indices

**Index Description:**
This data represents the effective yield of the ICE BofA 7-10 Year US Corporate Index, which is a subset of the ICE BofA US Corporate Master Index. It tracks the performance of US dollar denominated investment grade rated corporate debt publicly issued in the US domestic market, specifically including securities with a remaining term to maturity of greater than or equal to 7 years and less than 10 years.

**Note on Data:** When the last calendar day of the month falls on a weekend, weekend observations will occur as a result of month ending accrued interest adjustments.

## Trend Observation:
The yield has shown a declining trend over the most recent five trading days, moving from 4.96% on February 11 to 4.85% on February 16, 2026.
